== Potatoes ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{} of water.

Cut the @baking potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once boiled, pour the water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat with
@salt{1/2%tsp} and add the potatoes.

Cook until you can easily slip a #knife{} through, ~{15-18%minutes}. Once cooked,
drain in a #colander{}.

== Beef ==

While the potatoes cook, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and
discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment
after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Rogan Josh Curry ==

Once the mince has browned, stir in the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, and
@Rogan Josh curry paste{50%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{150%ml} for
the sauce (see pantry for both amounts).

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

== Naans ==

Put the @plain naans{2} onto a #baking tray{}.

Sprinkle them with a little water.

When you're almost ready to serve, pop them on the middle shelf of the oven to
warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful
at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Gently stir the cooked potato through the curry, adding a splash of water if
it's a little thick.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, spoon the curry into your bowls.

Scatter the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g} on top.

Spread the @butter{20%g} (see pantry for amount) over the naan and serve alongside
for dipping and scooping.

Enjoy!